Ted Odogwu, Kano The Kano State Government has approved the full resumption of JSS 1 and SS 1 students in both public and private schools in the state. The students, the state said, would resume on Monday, November 16, 2020 (today). The Commissioner for Education, Mallam Muhammad Kiru, who made the disclosure on Saturday, said, “All JSS 1 and SS1 students in boarding schools should resume Sunday the 15th of November 2020, while those in the day schools should resume Monday, November 16, 2020. “Subsequently, primary school pupils from one to six should also resume fully from next Monday, as against the earlier directives which categorised dates for their resumption.” The commissioner urged parents of students in those classes to ensure compliance. He directed school directors/principals and other stakeholders to prepare for resumption. Copyright PUNCH.
